Borimus was a brother of lollas and Mariandynus and son of king Upius who died young when hunting at harvest-time. He is com- memorated in a dirge-like song about husbandry. There was also a song known as Aletis, sung over the swings; this was the work of Theodorus of Colophon. And there was a Flute-piece of the Winepress, for the treading of the grapes; and another for the Winnowing‚ which is referred to by the comedy-writer Phrynichus in his Revellers, thus :
